<title>JAPAN: Canon shares rise as yen stabilises.</title>
<headline>Canon shares rise as yen stabilises.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Canon Inc climbed in heavy trade on Friday morning, encouraged by a market belief that the yen's recent rally has peaked, traders said.</p>
<p>At 0104 GMT, the price of the top printer maker was up 90 yen at 2,790 on turnover of 1.912 million shares, making it the third-most actively traded issue on the first section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange.</p>
